IRS990.MissionDesc: BUILDING GIRLS OF COURAGE, CONFIDENCE, AND CHARACTER, WHO MAKE THE WORLD A BETTER PLACE
IRS990.Desc: GIRL SCOUTS IS THE PREMIER LEADERSHIP DEVELOPMENT ORGANIZATION FOR GIRLS. WE BELIEVE IN THE POWER OF GIRLS AND AS PART OF THE LARGEST GIRL-LED ORGANIZATION IN THE WORLD, GIRLS DISCOVER THEIR INNER STRENGTHS, PASSIONS, AND TALENTS, WHILE DEVELOPING CORE LIFE SKILLS THAT EMPOWER THEM TO BE BOLD, COURAGEOUS LEADERS. WITH GIRL SCOUTS, GIRLS GET THE CHANCE TO DO BIG THINGS WHILE DISCOVERING THEIR SENSE OF SELF, CONNECTING WITH OTHERS IN AN INCREASINGLY DIVERSE WORLD, AND TAKING ACTION TO MAKE A LASTING IMPACT IN THEIR COMMUNITIES AND BEYOND.GIRL SCOUTS NORTH CAROLINA COASTAL PINES ("GSNCCP") IS ONE OF 112 GIRL SCOUT COUNCILS AND SERVES GIRLS IN 41 COUNTIES ACROSS CENTRAL AND EASTERN NORTH CAROLINA. REFLECTING THE RICH DIVERSITY OF THE COMMUNITIES IT SERVES, 46% OF THE GIRL MEMBERS OF GSNCCP IDENTIFIED THEMSELVES AS RACIALLY OR ETHNICALLY DIVERSE. IN 2017-2018, GSNCCP SERVED A TOTAL OF 25,728 GIRLS. PROGRAMS ARE A CORNERSTONE OF THE GIRL SCOUT LEADERSHIP EXPERIENCE. FROM BUILDING ROBOTS, TO LEARNING THE IMPORTANCE OF PERSONAL FINANCE OR CAMPING OUT UNDER THE STARS, GIRL MEMBERS EXPERIENCE A WIDE RANGE OF EXTRAORDINARY OPPORTUNITIES. GSNCCP HAS FIVE MAIN PROGRAM INITIATIVES: THE OUTDOORS, HEALTHY LIVING, STEM, CITIZENSHIP AND STEWARDSHIP, AND LEADERSHIP. THROUGH PROGRAM OPPORTUNITIES, GIRLS DISCOVER THE FUN, FRIENDSHIP AND POWER OF GIRLS TOGETHER. IN 2017-2018, ALL 41 COUNTIES IN OUR JURISDICTION WERE REPRESENTED AT MORE THAN 151 COUNCIL-SPONSORED EVENTS WHICH WERE ATTENDED BY 7,808 GIRLS.GSNCCP HAS A LONG HISTORY OF INCLUSION AND HAS BEEN COMMITTED TO MAKING THE ORGANIZATION ACCESSIBLE TO ALL GIRLS. BY REMOVING BARRIERS TO PARTICIPATION THROUGH COMMUNITY OUTREACH, OUR ORGANIZATION REACHES AT-RISK GIRLS, AGES FIVE THROUGH SEVENTEEN. PROGRAMS ARE DESIGNED TO TEACH GIRLS LIFE SKILLS THAT WILL POSITIVELY IMPACT THEIR FUTURE. IN 2017-2018, GSNCCP PROVIDED OUTREACH PROGRAMS TO 9,136 GIRLS FROM UNDER-RESOURCED FAMILIES.THE GIRL SCOUT GOLD AWARD STANDS FOR EXCELLENCE AND LEADERSHIP AND IS THE HIGHEST AND MOST PRESTIGIOUS ACHIEVEMENT IN GIRL SCOUTING. WHEN A GIRL SCOUT EMBARKS ON HER AWARD JOURNEY, SHE COMMITS TO TAKE ACTION AND CREATE A LASTING CHANGE IN HER COMMUNITY. SHE DEMONSTRATES SIGNIFICANT LEADERSHIP, PLANNING, NETWORKING AND ORGANIZATIONAL SKILLS IN COMPLETING HER PROJECT. IN 2017-2018, GSNCCP AWARDED 105 GIRLS WITH THE GOLD AWARD. SILVER AWARDS WERE EARNED BY 172 GIRLS AND BRONZE AWARDS WERE EARNED BY 685 GIRLS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COUNCIL CURRENTLY DOES NOT HAVE A WRITTEN POLICY BASED ON THE NATURE AND LOCATION OF THE EASEMENT. THE EASEMENT IS ON WETLANDS AND A FULL TIME STAFF PERSON LIVES ON THE ADJOINING PROPERTY AND OVERSEES THIS PROPERTY. ANY VIOLATIONS OF THE EASEMENT WOULD BE REPORTED IMMEDIATELY TO THE COUNCIL CEO. THE LAND IS INSPECTED ANNUALLY BY THE SANDHILLS AREA LAND TRUST BASED ON THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF THE CONSERVATION EASEMENT.
THERE HAS BEEN NO IMPACT ON THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS THIS YEAR OTHER THAN SALARY RELATED EXPENSES OF THE STAFF PERSON WHO MONITORS THE PROPERTY AND THE NUMBER OF HOURS WORKED.
THE ORGANIZATION'S ENDOWMENT FUNDS PROVIDE LONG-TERM SUPPORT FOR ITS ONGOING PROGRAMS.

IT IS THE COUNCIL'S POLICY TO EVALUATE ALL TAX POSITIONS AND TO IDENTIFY THOSE THAT MAY BE CONSIDERED UNCERTAIN. ALL IDENTIFIED MATERIAL TAX POSITIONS ARE ASSESSED AND MEASURED BY A MORE-LIKELY-THAN-NOT THRESHOLD TO DETERMINE IF THE BENEFIT OF ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITION SHOULD BE RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. MANAGEMENT BELIEVES THAT THE ORGANIZATION CONTINUES TO SATISFY THE REQUIREMENTS OF A TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATION AT SEPTEMBER 30, 2018. MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED ALL OTHER TAX POSITIONS THAT COULD HAVE A SIGNIFICANT EFFECT ON THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND DETERMINED THE ORGANIZATION HAD NO UNCERTAIN INCOME TAX POSITIONS AT SEPTEMBER 30, 2018 AND, ACCORDINGLY, NO LIABILITY HAS BEEN ACCRUED. ANY CHANGES IN THE AMOUNT OF A TAX POSITION ARE RECOGNIZED IN THE PERIOD THE CHANGE OCCURS.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: ASSISTANCE WITH GIRL SCOUT MEMBERSHIP, PROGRAMS, AND CAMP

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ASSISTANCE IS PROVIDED WITH RESPECT TO PARTICIPATION IN GIRL SCOUT ACTIVITIES ONLY IN THE FORM OF DISCOUNTS BASED ON ELIGIBILITY. SINCE FUNDS ARE NOT DIRECTLY PROVIDED, THERE IS NO NEED TO MONITOR THEM.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COUNCIL'S MEMBERSHIP INCLUDES COUNCIL DELEGATES ELECTED BY COUNTY CONSTITUENCIES, OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS OF THE CORPORATION, MEMBERS OF THE BOARD DEVELOPMENT COMMITTEE, NATIONAL COUNCIL DELEGATES, FORMER CHAIRS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF THE COUNCIL AS WELL AS ITS LEGACY COUNCILS LIVING WITHIN THE COUNCIL JURISDICTION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AS OUTLINED IN THE BYLAWS, ALL GOVERNING BOARD MEMBERS ARE ELECTED AT THE COUNCIL'S ANNUAL MEETING BY THE DELEGATE MEMBERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MEMBERS OF THE COUNCIL SHALL: A. ELECT THE OFFICERS OF THE COUNCIL; THE MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS; THE MEMBERS OF THE COUNCIL BOARD DEVELOPMENT COMMITTEE; AND, AS NECESSARY, THE NATIONAL COUNCIL DELEGATES AND NATIONAL COUNCIL DELEGATE ALTERNATES. B. DETERMINE GENERAL LINES OF DIRECTION FOR GIRL SCOUTING WITHIN THE JURISDICTION OF THE COUNCIL BY RECEIVING AND RESPONDING TO REPORTS AND INFORMATION FROM THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. C. INITIATE PROPOSALS FOR CONSIDERATION BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. D. AMEND THE ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION AND BYLAWS. E. TAKE ALL OTHER ACTION REQUIRING A MEMBERSHIP VOTE. F. CONDUCT SUCH OTHER BUSINESS AS MAY COME BEFORE THE MEMBERS

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANNUALLY THE AUDIT COMMITTEE MEETS WITH THE INDEPENDENT AUDIT FIRM TO REVIEW THE COMPLETED FORM 990. AFTER IT HAS BEEN APPROVED BY THE AUDIT COMMITTEE, THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE PROVIDED AN OPPORTUNITY TO REVIEW IT PRIOR TO IT BEING FILED WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, AND EMPLOYEES ARE REQUIRED TO COMPLETE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST DISCLOSURE FORM WHEN ELECTED OR HIRED, AND ANNUALLY THEREAFTER. IF A POTENTIAL CONFLICT ARISES DURING THE YEAR, IT IS THE STATED RESPONSIBILITY OF THE INDIVIDUAL TO BRING THE CONFLICT TO THE ATTENTION OF THE APPROPRIATE PERSON. THE DISCLOSURES ARE REVIEWED BY THE BOARD CHAIR, THE CEO, CFO, AND MANAGER AS APPLICABLE. IN THE EVENT OF A POTENTIAL CONFLICT, THAT PERSON WILL RECUSE THEMSELVES FROM ALL DISCUSSION AND/OR VOTE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION IS BASED ON A SALARY STUDY PERFORMED BY AN INDEPENDENT FIRM HIRED BY THE ORGANIZATION. COMPENSATION STUDIES INCLUDE REVIEW OF APPROPRIATE SALARY RANGES BASED ON POSITION DESCRIPTIONS AND RESPONSIBILITY LEVEL IN COMPARISON TO SIMILAR POSITIONS IN THE COUNCIL'S GEOGRAPHIC REGION. THE COUNCIL ALSO REVIEWS COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS SURVEYS OF OTHER LOCAL NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS. IN ADDITION, SALARIES, WAGES AND BENEFIT BUDGETED EXPENSES ARE ANNUALLY REVIEWED BY THE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
